# Mapping Strategy — MapStruct

## Core Rules
- Use **MapStruct** for DTO ↔ Entity mapping
- Avoid mapping logic inside controllers
- Never expose JPA entities outside the persistence layer

## Standard Mapper Pattern

```java
@Mapper(componentModel = "spring")
public interface EmployeeMapper {

    // Entity → Response DTO
    EmployeeResponseDto toDto(Employee entity);

    // Request DTO → Entity
    Employee toEntity(EmployeeRequestDto dto);

    // List mapping (auto-generated)
    List<EmployeeResponseDto> toDtoList(List<Employee> entities);

    // Custom field mapping
    @Mapping(source = "teamId", target = "team.id")
    @Mapping(target = "createdAt", ignore = true)
    Employee toEntity(CreateEmployeeRequest dto);

    // Update existing entity (partial update)
    @BeanMapping(nullValuePropertyMappingStrategy = NullValuePropertyMappingStrategy.IGNORE)
    void updateEntityFromDto(UpdateEmployeeRequest dto, @MappingTarget Employee entity);
}
```

## Best Practices
- Use `componentModel = "spring"` for Spring integration
- Use `@Mapping` for field name mismatches
- Use `@MappingTarget` for updating existing entities
- Use `nullValuePropertyMappingStrategy = IGNORE` for partial updates
- Keep mappers in the `mappers/` package
